commit.message: refactor(@angular-devkit/build-optimizer): correct implicit returns
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): correct implicit returns
refactor(@angular/cli): correct implicit returns
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-optimizer): minor type cleanup
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-optimizer): remove unused import purifier

refactor(@angular/cli): remove command type

It was really unused.

refactor(@schematics/angular): replace usage of unknown for any

Google3 is still on TypeScript 2.9.

refactor(@schematics/angular): Parameterize findModule

This commit modifies `findModule` to accept custom regular expressions
so that a different filename convention for Angular modules is allowed.
refactor: use common type for stdout and stderr
refactor: make the cli testable
refactor(@schematics/angular): make interaction with architect targets type safe
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): use async/await where possible
refactor(@angular/cli): automated JSON schema interface generation
refactor(@angular/pwa): automated JSON Schema generation

refactor: pin down all direct dependencies

This is so that CLI users get the same direct dependency versions that were tested on the CI.
refactor(@schematics/schematics): automated JSON schema interface generation
refactor(@schematics/angular): automated JSON schema generation
refactor(@schematics/update): add automated JSON schema generation
refactor(@angular/cli): remove parseJsonFile and add options to parseJson instead
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-optimizer): remove unused helper function

refactor(@angular/cli): rename project to workspace and clean up

Removed unnecessary fields in interfaces, added some comments. Overall QoL.

feat(@angular/cli): add --helpJson (or --help-json) too all commands

And other refactors.

The interface for the JSON is available in command.ts (the CommandDescription).
refactor(@angular/cli): use smart default instead of overwriting args
refactor(@angular/cli): rename getset command to deprecated

refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): clean up style webpack config

Clean up several parts of the styles config and also removed the dependency on `postcss-url`
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): avoid double caching of files
refactor: move isJsonObject to json namespace

refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): mute internal reporters (#11238)

* refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): mute internal reporters when
other reporters are configured

internal Karma reporters should suppress output when user-defined
reporters are configured to prevent extrananeous error reporting for
failed tests

refactor: cleanup and better documentation / comments (hidden from release log)

refactor: remove `flatModuleId` and `flatModuleOutFile` from library tsconfig

The autogenerated fiellds are no longer required following this PR https://github.com/dherges/ng-packagr/pull/1024

This has been released in `ng-packagr` `v4.1.0`
refactor(@angular-devkit/core): cleanup ajv initialization

refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): remove unnecessary stylus-loader workaround

Remove unnecessary stylus-loader workaround. Issue, from which this workaround originates, is resolved. Link to issue in stylus-loader: https://github.com/shama/stylus-loader/issues/189
refactor: fix typo

refactor(@ngtools/webpack): expose TS TypeChecker from NG compiler plugin

Expose the TypeScript Program created by the plugin, so that it can be used in custom platform transformers.
refactor(@angular-devkit/schematics-cli): update bazel build file
refactor: remove extra `.` in error message

refactor(@angular-devkit/schematics): add a BaseWorkflow which implements logic

And receives in its constructor the enginehost and registry. This simplifies the creation
of the NodeWorkflow, or later on the Google3Workflow etc, since all the duplicate logic
is now in a single base class.

This is yak shaving for internal stuff.
refactor(@angular/cli): use compiler-cli peer dep to check typescript

refactor(@angular/cli): remove a tslint:disable:no-global-tslint-disable no-any

Not entirely removed the usage of any but its a step in the right direction.
refactor(@angular-devkit/architect): use updated workspace api
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): minor CSS processing cleanup
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): allow webpack plugin to use default host
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): use webpack input filesystem as default host

refactor: fix types to remove any

require() returns any so we were missing some typing errors.
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): support function-based host file replacement

refactor: types for content should be a pure template

Limitting it to a subset of JSON values is limiting. Templates can call functions,
list arrays, access classes, etc.
refactor(@angular-devkit/build-angular): use plugin for file replacement
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): support file replacement without copying
refactor: fix path for `workspace-loader`
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): remove unneeded tsconfig
refactor(@ngtools/webpack): cleanup webpack types and use tapPromise

refactor: add tslint-sonarts and a lot of tslint rules

This should clean up the code a bit.

Note: at first I added the no-useless-cast rule, but after getting frustrated
with it (as it has many false positive), I decided to remove the rule but some
useless casts were removed so I let those in the PR.

refactor: add no-floating-promises lint rule to project

With fixes; new now handles the parent initialize, visitor_spec now errors on
rejection, and nothing in the writeI18nOutFile() function was async so removed
the promise there entirely.
refactor: remove redundant `error` in catch
refactor(@angular-devkit/schematics): cleanup call implementations

refactor(@angular/cli):  remove extra `await`

An async function always wraps the return value in a Promise. Using return await just adds extra time before the overreaching promise is resolved without changing the semantics.
refactor(@schematics/angular): `skipPackageJson` is optional for application schematic
refactor(@angular-devkit/schematics): simplify move rule
refactor(@schematics/angular): minor refactorings

refactor: remove usage of Buffer constructor

Its being deprecated in Node 10.4. The replacements are available in Node 8 so
its all good.
